resultSet.errorTitle: The layout or sizing of this page causes horizontal scrolling.
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 1.4.8 Visual Presentation
resultSet.resultTitle: Avoid layouts that result in horizontal scroll
resultSet.errorDescription: This page is too wide, causing horizontal scrolling (at the tested viewport size). Horizontal scrolling will cause difficulties for users with low vision, especially if they have their monitor set to a low resolution. Review HTML, CSS and page element sizes to ensure 100% width is not exceeded.

resultSet.errorTitle: This link has no text inside it.

resultSet.resultTitle: Make sure that link text (and the alternate text for any images that are used as links) describes the destination or purpose of the link.
resultSet.errorDescription: The text inside of a link informs the user of the purpose or destination of the link. Add text within this link to make it usable and understandable for all users

resultSet.errorTitle: This element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA).
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 1.4.6 Contrast (Enhanced)
resultSet.resultTitle: Avoid using color as the only visual means of conveying information
resultSet.errorDescription: This element has insufficient contrast between the foreground color (the text) and the background color when measured against the WCAG 2.0 Level AAA requirements. Sufficient color contrast is important for users who have low-vision or are color-blind, because text with a low contrast ratio may be difficult or impossible for such users to see. Increase the contrast of this content. This can be done by adjusting the color(s) used by either the foreground content or background content ‚Äì or both.

resultSet.errorTitle: These links have the same text but different destinations.
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level A: 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context)
Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 2.4.9 Link Purpose (Link Only)
resultSet.resultTitle: Don't reuse the same link text for links that have different destinations
resultSet.errorDescription: This link has the same text as another link that goes to a different place. Using the same text for multiple links which point to different pages is ambiguous and may be confusing for assistive technology users, or for users who have a cognitive disability. Link text should tell the user where they will go if they follow the link. If two links on a page go to two different destinations, use different link text that accurately and concisely describes their destination.

standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 1.4.8 Visual Presentation
resultSet.resultTitle: Set a `line-height` (leading) that is at least one and a half times the current font size.
resultSet.errorDescription: This content's line height is insufficent to properly display the computed element font size. Line height that is less than 150% of the computed element font size limits content readability for people with dyslexia, low vision, cognitive impairments or learning disabilities. Set the `line-height` for this content to a value of 1.5 or higher. Using a proportional, unitless value like 1.5 or 150% will ensure that the line-height scales if the user zooms the browser window.

resultSet.errorTitle: These headings are not structured in a hierarchical manner.
standards: Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level A: 1.3.1 Info and Relationships
Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0, Level AAA: 2.4.10 Section Headings
resultSet.resultTitle: Make sure that headings are in the right order for the content.
resultSet.errorDescription: The heading structure of this page does not effectively communicate the structure of the content on it. Heading elements provide important benefits: they act as wayfinding cues for in-page navigation, they contribute to page content summaries, and they provide context to the content below them. To do so effectively, headings should follow the `<h1>` to `<h6>` hierarchy and they should not skip levels. Restructure the document's heading order so it uses a clear, ordered, and intuitive hierarchy. Ensure there are no gaps between each numbered heading level and the next.

focAll.what: Discrepancy between elements that should be and that are Tab-focusable

focOp.what: Operable elements that cannot be Tab-focused and vice versa

styleDiff.what: Heading, link, and button style inconsistencies

w:AA.4_1_2.H91.A.Empty.what: Link element has an id attribute but no href attribute or text

57.what: Link has no text inside it

r3.what: Element id attribute value is not unique

duplicate-id-active.what: id attribute value of the active element is not unique

r57.what: Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark

region.what: Some page content is not contained by landmarks

r66.what: Text contrast less than AAA requires

color-contrast-enhanced.what: Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA)

95.what: Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA)

r69.what: Text outside widget has subminimum contrast

e:AA.1_4_3.G18.Fail.what: Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1

r73.what: Paragraph of text has insufficient line height

r87.what: First focusable element is not a link to the main content

aria-allowed-attr.what: ARIA attribute is invalid for the role of its element

hidden-content.what: Some content is hidden and therefore may not be testable for accessibility

identical-links-same-purpose.what: Links with the same accessible name may serve dissimilar purposes

css-orientation-lock.what: CSS media query locks display orientation

focus-order-semantics.what: Focusable element has no active role

landmark-unique.what: Landmark has a role and an accessible name that are identical to another

w:AA.1_1_1.H67.2.what: Image marked as decorative may be informative

w:AA.1_3_1.H48.what: Navigation links are not coded as a list

155.what: Headings are not structured in a hierarchical manner

w:AA.4_1_2.H91.A.Placeholder.what: Link has text but no href, id, or name attribute

a:alt_duplicate.what: Two images near each other have the same text alternative

a:link_redundant.what: Adjacent links go to the same URL

a:noscript.what: noscript element may fail to contain an accessible equivalent or alternative

28.what: Layout or sizing of the page causes horizontal scrolling

73.what: Link text is too generic to communicate the purpose or destination
